# XERO08 Export Error: Report PDF Is Too Large

If you see the error message **“XERO08 Export Error: PDF of report is too large to export (>10MB). Please reach out to Concierge for additional assistance.”**, it means the report PDF exceeds Xero’s 10MB attachment size limit.

Xero does not allow attachments larger than 10MB.

---

## Why the XERO08 Export Error Happens

The XERO08 export error occurs when:

- The generated PDF of the report is larger than **10MB**, and  
- Xero rejects the attachment during export  

Large PDFs are typically caused by:

- High-resolution receipt images  
- Multiple large attachments on a single report  

---

## How to Fix the XERO08 Export Error

Please reach out to **Concierge** for assistance.

We’ll help review the report, determine the cause of the oversized PDF, and provide guidance on how to successfully export it to Xero.

---

# FAQ

## Can I reduce the PDF size myself?

You may try removing unnecessary or duplicate attachments from the report. However, if the error persists, contact Concierge for support.

## Does this error affect other exports?

Only reports with PDFs larger than 10MB will fail. Smaller reports will export normally.
